Not long ago, Abraaj was one of the world’s highest-profile private-equity firms. We take a look at its spectacular downfall, and the fate of its charismatic boss, Arif Naqvi. This weekend Australian voters will elect a new parliament. How can politicians win back a disillusioned electorate? And why do sausages feature so strongly on voting day? Runtime: 21min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn